00:00:09.000 --> 00:00:15.000
Swimming Jewels --Nishikigoi Carp-- 

00:00:19.319 --> 00:00:25.319
The carp is the oldest fish that has been bred in the history 
of the human race culture.

00:00:25.867 --> 00:00:31.867
Carp's place of origin is Central Asia.
That has  entered Japan via China and Korea.

00:00:32.601 --> 00:00:38.601
It is people of Niigata Japan that improved the kind to the Nishikigoi carp as for this original carp.

00:00:49.366 --> 00:00:55.366
The carp with a red head was born about 200 years ago by the mutation in the carp that had been bred as for food at that time. 

00:01:00.372 --> 00:01:06.372
They hybridized that red headed carp and made a red carp and a white carp.

00:01:04.991 --> 00:01:11.991
In addition, hybridization was invented and nowaday's Nishikigoi with beautiful pattern was invented repeatedly. 

00:01:12.421 --> 00:01:18.421
From at that time,various Nishikigois are made in various parts of Japan. 

00:01:18.366 --> 00:01:25.366
The Nishikigoi that was a peculiar aquarium fish to Japan came to be called a country fish in Japan. 

00:01:38.381 --> 00:01:43.381
Various ponds : Japanese traditional style

00:01:45.326 --> 00:01:51.326
Various ponds : Concrete pond

00:01:54.614 --> 00:02:00.614
Water tank breeding at the veranda has increased because of the advancement of the breeding technology. 

00:02:00.465 --> 00:02:06.465
In the favor, the Nishikigoi came to be able to enjoy easily in the room, and came to merge in our life. 

00:02:09.473 --> 00:02:15.473
Various kinds of the Nishikigoi : "Kohaku( "Red &amp; White")"

00:02:16.440 --> 00:02:24.440
This "Kohaku" is the most popular kind in the Nishikigoi.
Its looks like the national flag of Japan.

00:02:31.184 --> 00:02:36.184
The Nishikigoi that has a red and black pattern entered the white ground is called "Taisho San-shoku(Taisho San-ke)".

00:02:36.407 --> 00:02:42.407
It means "Taisho style Three Colors (or three colored hairs)".
*"Taisho" is an era name of Japan.

00:02:40.961 --> 00:02:45.961
This magnificent kind is Nishikigoi's typical kind with Kohaku. 

00:02:51.921 --> 00:02:56.921
Patterned red and white on black ground one is called "Showa San-shoku ("Showa style Three Colored")".

00:02:57.848 --> 00:03:03.848
This kind which has dynamic feeling also : in a typical kind.

00:03:00.220 --> 00:03:07.220
These three kinds that "Showa" and "Kohaku" and "Taisho" are called "Gosanke (means "Big Three")" .

00:03:09.895 --> 00:03:14.895
The carp that queues up a black pattern in a white or red ground color is called "Bekko ("Tortoiseshell")". 

00:03:11.635 --> 00:03:19.635
"Shiro-Bekko (White Bekko)" and "Aka-Bekko (Red Bekko)"

00:03:21.076 --> 00:03:27.076
That a part of black ground came off in white is called "Shiro-utsuri (undyed on a field of black) ". 

00:03:33.857 --> 00:03:40.857
That a part of black ground came off in red is called "Hi-utsuri (red-undyed on a field of black) ". 

00:03:42.600 --> 00:03:49.600
This is the "Asagi (Japanese pale blue)".
It has scales with hemming on Japanese pale blue ground color (it seems the net pattern).

00:03:52.314 --> 00:04:00.314
The one which has scales only on the back is called "Shu-sui ("Autumn leaves that reflects in surface of the green water)"

00:04:00.654 --> 00:04:03.000
The one which has no scales is called "Doitsu-goi (German Koi)".

00:04:03.893 --> 00:04:10.893
The "Koromo ("Dress")" has scales with hemming black or indigo blue on the red ground color.

00:04:14.006 --> 00:04:21.006
The "Goshiki ("Five colors")" has the fine red pattern on scales with hemming  as same as "Asagi".

00:04:25.318 --> 00:04:32.318
The "Ochiba-shigure ("The autumn leaves falling down like a rain")" has the light brown pattern on the background as same as "Asagi"

00:04:36.632 --> 00:04:42.632
The "Kumon-ryu (means "Nine Crests Dragon")" has the black pattern on the background as same as "Shu-sui" .

00:04:46.644 --> 00:04:50.644
Additional red pattern with "Kumon-ryu", it called "Beni-Kumon-Ryu ("Beni" means "Red")".

00:04:52.129 --> 00:04:58.129
It called "Gin-rin ("Silver Scales")" which has shining scales.

00:04:58.398 --> 00:05:03.398
And also this word "Gin-rin" is used as a kind of preposition.
"Gin-rin Showa"
"Gin-rin Goshiki"
"Gin-rin San-shoku"

00:05:03.666 --> 00:05:09.666
"Ohgon ("Gold")".

00:05:09.272 --> 00:05:14.272
"Purachina ("Platinum")".

00:05:15.046 --> 00:05:20.046
"Kujaku ("Peacock")" has the pattern as same as "Goshiki" with shining scales.

00:05:21.119 --> 00:05:26.119
The carp which has shining scales is called the "Hikari-mono" generically.

